In this interview, Vice President Mike Pence praises the leadership and efforts of Governor Abbott and the state of Texas in response to the devastating effects of Hurricane Harvey. He commends the volunteers and first responders who have risked their lives to rescue fellow citizens. Pence emphasizes that the focus is on rescue and that the storm is still dangerous. He assures listeners that the federal government, along with state and local officials, is working to provide support and resources. Pence also mentions that President Trump is visiting Texas to show solidarity with affected families and ensure that federal agencies are doing everything they can to assist in the rescue and recovery efforts. He encourages listeners to support and donate to volunteer organizations providing aid on the ground.